CHOLERA, DIARRHEA AND DYSENTERY UPDATE (51): MEXICO (FEDERAL DISTRICT, HIDALGO) CHOLERA SUSPECTED
*************************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Sat 28 Sep 2013
Source: ABC News, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/cholera-kills-sickens-mexico-20403130


Mexico's health authorities say cholera has killed one person and sickened at least another 9 in central Mexico.

Mexico's Health Department says 2 cases were detected in Mexico City and the rest in the nearby state of Hidalgo, where one person died. The department on Fri 27 Sep 2013, declared a health emergency for Hidalgo. Authorities said it's the same cholera strain that is sickening hundreds of people in Caribbean countries, including Cuba and the Dominican Republic.

Mexico City health authorities say they have intensified their surveillance of water treatment plants and water tanks and have launched a campaign to educate people about preventing infection.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
