******
[2]
Date: Tue 1 Oct 2013
Source: Volkskrant [in Dutch, machine trans., edited]
http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2664/Nieuws/article/detail/3519157/2013/10/01/Uitbraak-cholera-na-overstromingen-in-Mexico.dhtml


After weeks of heavy rains in Mexico, the number of cholera cases has risen to 44. The Mexican Ministry of Health reports that in the state of Hidalgo 33 suspected cases are being examined.

The infectious disease has so far claimed one life. According to Health Minister Mercedes Juan, there is no talk of an epidemic. Last week [week of 23 Sep 2013] an emergency program was implemented and doctors were sent to the affected region in the center of the country.

The 1st case of cholera had already occurred before the beginning of severe weather, but the shortage of clean drinking water in flooded areas could worsen the situation.

--
